<taxonomicName id="9DF31AB1FFAF98310302A9FD70A8FA6B" authorityName="Sheals" authorityYear="1962" box="[594,909,1440,1466]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Cosmolaelaps" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rectangularis">
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF98310302A9FD70A8FA6B" box="[594,909,1440,1466]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Cosmolaelaps rectangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new species from Patagonia, 
<collectingCountry id="22E421A2FFAF98310454A9FD7653FA6B" box="[1284,1398,1440,1466]" name="Argentina" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, on the basis of 
<specimenCount id="4CF5AABBFFAF9831004DA99872BDFA0F" box="[285,408,1476,1503]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
specimen collected on an unspecified substrate. Subsequently, 
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFAF9831050AA99877CEFA0E" author="Costa, M." box="[1114,1259,1476,1503]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref13901" refString="Costa, M. (1968) Little known and new litter-inhabiting Laelapine mites (Acari, Mesostigmata) from Israel. Israel Journal of Zoology, 17, 1 - 30." type="journal article" year="1968">Costa (1968)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed the species based on female specimens and described the male of this species for the first time from 
<collectingCountry id="22E421A2FFAF98310598A9B5762FF9D3" box="[1224,1290,1512,1538]" name="Israel" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Israel</collectingCountry>
. This species has been recorded from North America, Europe and Asia from soil-litter or ant nests and is now recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="22E421A2FFAF98310402AA5176B8F9F7" box="[1362,1437,1548,1574]" name="Russia" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Russia</collectingCountry>
for the first time, from a nest of 
<taxonomicName id="9DF31AB1FFAF98310351AA6C71ADF99A" box="[513,648,1585,1611]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Myrmica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="6887BD20FFAF98310351AA6C7143F99B" box="[513,614,1585,1610]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="501">Myrmica</emphasis>
sp
</taxonomicName>
.. Our newly collected material agrees very well with the redescription given by 
<bibRefCitation id="3E621CC3FFAF98310054AA0872BEF9BE" author="Costa, M." box="[260,411,1620,1647]" pageId="15" pageNumber="501" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref13901" refString="Costa, M. (1968) Little known and new litter-inhabiting Laelapine mites (Acari, Mesostigmata) from Israel. Israel Journal of Zoology, 17, 1 - 30." type="journal article" year="1968">Costa (1968)</bibRefCitation>
. This species can be readily recognised by the 39 pairs of spatulate-mucronate-tricarinate dorsal setae.
</paragraph>
